cs.IT, cs.ITP, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication, specifically investigating the capacity and coding for a binary-input binary-output channel with feedback and input constraints. This falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The paper also introduces new ideas such as message history and message splitting, which could potentially fall under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of dynamic programming optimization and coding schemes could also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
